<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISCOVERIES: INSIDE & OUT; SEASIDE SEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CYNDI Y. NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One look at Sea Design Furniture's Steamer chair and lounger, and sitting by 
the sea will become the order of the day. 
</P>
<P>
 The chair and lounger, designed and manufactured by the San Clemente company, 
are made of teak. Both are fully collapsible for easy storing and transporting, 
and the joint mechanisms are rustproof. 
</P>
<P>
 Each piece of the chair is shaped by hand, so the seat and back conform to the 
body. 
</P>
<P>
 "It has a timeless feel, from the '30s and '40s," said Jan Tucker, owner of 
Sea Design. "It always reminds me of Cary Grant and 'An Affair to Remember."' 
</P>
<P>
 Tucker said she and her husband designed the chair because they liked the 
loungers on the Queen Mary. "Those chairs looked good, but there was no 'beef' 
to them. So we modified it to what we wanted." 
</P>
<P>
 The chair is $949, the lounger $1,149. The Sea Design showroom is at 1504 
Avenida de la Estrella, No. G. For information, call (714) 498-9107. Harvest 
Dishes 
</P>
<P>
 Ceramist Barbara Eigen's earthenware looks almost good enough to eat. 
</P>
<P>
 Specializing in serving pieces in the shape of fruits and vegetables, Eigen 
made a slight departure for her latest works, sold under her Eigen Arts label. 
</P>
<P>
 "The squash tureen and lidded casseroles are more decorative, more whimsical 
than my usual pieces, but they still function as serving pieces," said Eigen, 
49, who started in a SoHo loft in 1977. She moved her factory and studio to New 
Jersey about five years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 All of Eigen's wares are dishwasher-safe and can be used for cooking in a slow 
oven. "I use them every day," she said,  
</P>
<P>
 Each piece is hand-painted and finished with a nontoxic glaze for sheen. 
</P>
<P>
 Eigen's collection, with pieces priced from $20 and up, can be purchased in 
Orange County at I. Magnin in Newport Beach, or by calling Eigen at (201) 
798-7310. Pet Project 
</P>
<P>
 The loss of Chef, her 13-year-old cat, a little more than a year ago, inspired 
Diana Laufer to create a pet memorial candle. 
</P>
<P>
 After an unsuccessful search for an affordable tribute, Laufer, an author and 
illustrator for children's books, decided to design something to help deal with 
her grief. 
</P>
<P>
 "I found tombstones and plaques, but nothing unique," said Laufer, owner/art 
director of Design Street Studios in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Furry Angel ($10.99) is a wax-filled glass tumbler with a silk-screened label 
that depicts ethereal animals flying around a poem. It comes with a card that 
suggests a candle-lighting ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
 For information or to order, call (213) 939-6680 or write Furry Angel, 8391 
Beverly Blvd., No. 263, Los Angeles, CA 90048. 
</P>
