shape. The Stephen S. Wise Temple in Bel-Air, the second largest U.S. 
synagogue, is going to move the nation's only Reform Jewish high school there 
(B13). . . . The busy temple had 8,500 adults and 2,000 children at the last 
High Holy Days services. Michael Arkush 
