ultimately may determine if the Los Angeles City Council helped foster a policy 
of police brutality. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. District Judge J. Spencer Letts dismissed the jury when he learned that a 
key plaintiff witness was unable to testify and that another did not have 
firsthand knowledge of what she going to be asked about.  
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit, filed on behalf of 4-year-old Johanna Trevino, stems from the 
fatal police shooting of her father, Javier, and two other men during an 
attempted robbery of a McDonald's in Sunland on Feb. 12, 1990.  
</P>
<P>
 The trial was reset for Dec. 6. It is the second mistrial within a year in the 
case. 
