<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; RECALL PETITION DRIVE COULD BEGIN SOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As early as this weekend, Ventura residents could begin circulating petitions 
to recall Councilwoman Rosa Lee Measures, a resident who is organizing the 
recall drive said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 East county homeowner Elaina Fletcher in August began her effort to oust 
Measures from office, claiming the council member abused the public trust by 
backing a development proposal by friend and business associate Ron Hertel. 
</P>
<P>
 Hertel wanted to give the city 94 acres south of California 126 and $2 million 
toward building a regional park at the site, in exchange for permission to 
build 437 residences on a city-owned lemon orchard at Telegraph Road and Petit 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Measures supported the proposal, but later found she had a conflict of 
interest because she owned a share in property situated within 2,500 feet of 
the proposed park site. 
</P>
<P>
 Fletcher argues that Measures should not have lobbied for Hertel's park-swap 
proposal because of the conflict of interest. 
</P>
<P>
 Fletcher said she is relieved to finally have the petitions approved by the 
city clerk. She said she and other residents will begin circulating the 
petitions by mid-week at the latest. 
</P>
<P>
 "The real work starts now," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fletcher has up to 160 days to collect 8,589 signatures -- the amount needed 
to call a special election on the recall. 
</P>
<P>
 Measures was not available for comment. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
