<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; OLIVAS ADOBE A FUN HALLOWEEN HAUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Looking for a bone-chilling Halloween tour that's not too wicked for the 
toddlers? 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura's Olivas Adobe believes it has just the answer -- a 15-minute, guided 
scramble through the old ranching house, trussed up to spook the children and 
at least amuse the grown-ups. 
</P>
<P>
 The 15-minute tours will run on Saturday at the adobe, 4200 Olivas Park Drive, 
from 6:30 to 8:30 p.m., leaving every 15 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $3 for adults, $2 for children, and are available at the door. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call 658-4726. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
