<P>
MAN SHOT TO DEATH IN ANAHEIM STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are investigating the fatal shooting of a man Friday in the 1400 block 
of South Allec Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, whose identity has not been released, was shot twice in the street 
just after 9 a.m., according to Anaheim Sgt. Charles Chavez. He was pronounced 
dead at UCI Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that the victim had been talking to a man in the street 
and that they had not appeared to be arguing. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooter then got into a nearby parked car and drove away, Chavez said. 
