<P>
 Golden West College is urging new students or students returning after a 
one-semester absence or more to register now for the spring semester. 
</P>
<P>
 The community college is issuing applications for enrollment at its admissions 
and records office on campus, 15744 Golden West St. Applications may be picked 
up Mondays through Thursdays between 8 a.m. and 7 p.m. and Fridays between 8 
a.m. and 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Late applicants risk long registration lines and closed classes, college 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
