<P>
TWO POLICE VEHICLES COLLIDE DURING CHASE; OFFICER HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A motorcycle officer was injured Friday when he collided with a police car as 
both vehicles chased the driver of a stolen car. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Howard Eisenberg, 41, suffered facial cuts and a broken nose in the 
collision near West Coast Highway and Riverside Avenue about 3:30 p.m., police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Another motorcycle officer had begun the chase after seeing the driver make an 
illegal U-turn on West Coast Highway near Newport Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car, a Mitsubishi Eclipse Turbo reported stolen from Big 
Bear Lake on Oct. 6, led police in and out of Costa Mesa, with the two 
motorcycles and police car in pursuit. 
</P>
<P>
 A short time after the police car and motorcycle collided, the fleeing vehicle 
was trapped by other officers in the 2000 block of Aliso Avenue in Newport 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Andy Gonis said the driver, Christopher Foster, 21, of San Bernardino, 
ran from the car and tossed away a bag containing a loaded weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 He was tracked by helicopter and arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger, Adrian Rosu, 22, of Grand Terrace, also was arrested on suspicion 
of auto theft. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonis said that "additional evidence possibly linking them to other crimes" 
was recovered from the car. 
</P>
<P>
 Both men were being held at the Newport Beach Jail. 
</P>
