<TEXT>
<P>
 CareLine Inc. said Friday that it has completed its acquisition of Metro 
Ambulance Service Inc. in Marietta, Ga.The company refused to disclose terms of 
the sale. The Irvine-based ambulance service company also said that it has 
terminated its letters of intent to buy TEK Ambulance and Rescue Eight 
Paramedic Services, both of which serve the Chicago area. Since CareLine was 
formed two years ago, it has made 18 acquisitions and expanded its services to 
nine states. The company says it is now the second-largest provider of 
ambulance services in the nation. 
