<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEX PARTNER WASN'T AN EVIL TWIN, JURY SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man charged with impersonating his twin in order to have sex with the 
brother's girlfriend was cleared by a jury that deliberated just five minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Lamont Hough, 24, of Roosevelt, N.Y., was found not guilty Thursday of 
criminal impersonation. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman had said she called police when she realized that the man she had 
had sex with was not her boyfriend. But defense attorney Peter Borgiorno said 
the jury of five women and one man did not believe the woman was fooled. 
</P>
