<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; CAL LUTHERAN MARKS ITS 30TH 
ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran University celebrates its 30th anniversary today, with plans for 
homecoming festivities ranging from a parade in Thousand Oaks to a nostalgic 
gathering of alumni on the set of the old television show "Gunsmoke." 
</P>
<P>
 The parade begins at 11 a.m. and proceeds down Memorial Parkway to Kingsmen 
Park for a picnic at 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 At 1 p.m., the Cal Lutheran Kingsmen face off against the Pomona-Pitzer 
football team. 
</P>
<P>
 After the game, alumni from all classes are scheduled to gather for a 
homecoming party featuring hayrides, food, dancing and music. The post-game 
party begins at 4:30 p.m. at the Cal Lutheran stables, north of Olsen Road. 
</P>
<P>
 The theme is "Return to Dodge City" because the old television show "Gunsmoke" 
was filmed in the Wildwood development near the campus. The old set will be 
re-created at the stables for the party. 
</P>
<P>
 Reunions for the classes of 1964-65, 1969, 1974, 1984 and 1989 will be held at 
the homes of alumni and faculty at 8:30 p.m. Information: the University 
Relations office at 493-3151. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
