COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; MOTORCYCLISTS TO CARRY TOYS TO ORANGEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Motorcyclists are invited to join a convoy carrying toys and donations Sunday 
to a home for abused and neglected children in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 The benefit is expected to draw more than 300 motorcyclists, said Pete Linton, 
an Irvine police investigator who heads the event. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to gathering toys for the Orangewood Children's Home, the ride 
will honor Tom and Marcy Smith, an Irvine couple killed last summer riding on 
the Oregon-Washington border. 
</P>
<P>
 The event -- sponsored by a chapter of the Gold Wing Road Riders Assn. and the 
Irvine Police Assn. -- is open to all makes of motorcycles. 
</P>
<P>
 Riders should bring a $1 donation and a toy gift for the children, who range 
in age from infants to teen-agers. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration will take place from 8 to 10 a.m. at the La Quinta Inn, 14972 
Sand Canyon Ave., Irvine. 
