By NANCY HSU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mother and four children are recovering from injuries sustained when their 
van collided with a car Thursday afternoon, UCI Medical Center officials said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Laurie K. Reed, 27, of Huntington Beach and her 5-year-old daughter, Jessie, 
are listed in good condition, while Cathy, 9, is listed in fair condition at 
UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Reed's other two children who were injured in the accident -- an infant and a 
3-year-old -- were treated and released to their father Thursday night, said 
Lorraine Neher, a hospital spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that Reed was driving a Volkswagen van eastbound on 
Warner Avenue when she ran a red light at Springdale Street, hitting a Camaro 
driven by Ryan Benz of Huntington Beach, according to Mike Corcoran of the 
Huntington Beach Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Benz was taken to Huntington Beach Medical Center, but a hospital spokeswoman 
said he was released that same night. 
</P>
<P>
 The children were not wearing seat belts. No citations were issued, but police 
are still investigating, Corcoran said. NANCY HSU 
