<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: VALLEYWIDE; HALLOWEEN FESTIVITIES: PARTIES AND BENEFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saturday's local celebrations for Halloween include: 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas Days Pumpkin Festival will sponsor a Halloween parade down Calabasas 
Road through Old Town Calabasas at dusk. Included will be a "safe trick or 
treat" opportunity for costumed children. Proceeds will benefit charities. Call 
(818) 225-2227. 
</P>
<P>
 Calahan Elementary School, 18722 Knapp St., Northridge, sponsors a Halloween 
festival with a "Spooky Space Station," moon bounce, pumpkin-carving contest, 
magician, fortune teller, dunk tank, games and food from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. Game 
tickets are 25 cents each at the door. Call (818) 886-4612. 
</P>
<P>
 Common Grounds, 9250 Reseda Blvd., Northridge, will have a Halloween dress-up 
party with the band Diga Jiga at 9 p.m. Call (818) 882-3666. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale Public Library, 222 E. Harvard St., will have a free Halloween haunt 
with stories and scares for ages 3 and older from 2 to 3 p.m. Costumes 
encouraged. Call (818) 548-2035. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles Zoo, in Griffith Park at the junction of the Ventura and Golden 
State freeways, presents "Boo at the Zoo" from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. today and 
Sunday. Featured will be zoo animals "stomping and chomping" pumpkins, a guided 
tour of night-loving species and the chance to create a beastly mask or owl 
puppet. Activities are free with paid zoo admission. Zoo admission is $8.25 
general, $5.25 seniors, $3.25 children aged 2 to 12. Free for children under 2. 
Zoo hours are 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Call (213) 666-4090. 
</P>
<P>
 New Age Singles, for ages 50 and older, offers a Halloween costume dance party 
at 7 p.m. at Leo Baeck Temple, 1300 N. Sepulveda Blvd., Bel-Air. Prize for best 
male and female costumes. Admission is $8 members, $10 non-members. Call (818) 
780-5912. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge Recreation Center, 18300 Lemarsh St., sponsors a haunted house from 
7 to 10 p.m. and 6 to 10 p.m. Sunday and Monday. A carnival featuring contests, 
games, booths and refreshments runs from noon to 4 p.m. today. Admission to 
haunted house $3; children ages 6 and younger free when accompanied by adult. 
Admission to the carnival is $2 and includes 10 game tickets. Call (818) 
349-7341. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Henry Middle School, 17340 San Jose St., Granada Hills, will have a 
pumpkin patch and haunted house from 10 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. today through Monday. 
Admission is free. Call 818-363-7401. 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda Recreation Center, 18411 Victory Blvd., will have a haunted house from 
5:30 to 9:30 p.m. today through Monday. Admission is $1. Call (818) 881-3882. 
</P>
<P>
 Sepulveda Unitarian Universalist Society, 9550 Haskell Ave., North Hills, 
sponsors a free family Halloween theater, featuring screenings of "The Legend 
of Sleepy Hollow" and "The Tell-Tale Heart" at 7 p.m. Call (818) 894-9251. 
</P>
<P>
 Shadow Ranch Recreation Center, 22633 Vanowen St., West Hills, will have a 
Halloween carnival with food, game booths, rides and prizes 11 a.m. to 9 p.m. 
today and Sunday. Admission is free. Ride tickets are 50 cents each. Call (818) 
883-3637. 
</P>
<P>
 Six Flags Magic Mountain, 26101 Magic Mountain Parkway, near Valencia, 
presents "Halloween Fright Fest" with live entertainment, ghosts, goblins, 
mazes and special effects from 10 a.m. to 8 p.m. today and Sunday. The 
roller-coaster Psyclone will run backward during the event. Admission is $28 
general, $15 for children and $18 for seniors. Call (818) 367-5965. 
</P>
<P>
 Spooky House, 23812 Friar St., Woodland Hills, features Woodland Hills Youth 
Club spirits who will lead guests on a terror tour of a specially engineered 
torture chamber from 6 to 11:30 p.m. today, and 6 to 10 p.m. Sunday and Monday. 
For one hour each day, beginning at twilight, the show will be toned down for 
younger spirits. Admission is $2 general, $1 children. (818) 888-8570. 
</P>
<P>
 Studio City Recreation Center, 12621 Rye St., will have a haunted house from 5 
to 10 p.m. today and Sunday. Admission is $3. Call (818) 769-4415. 
</P>
<P>
 Universal CityWalk, 1000 Universal Center Drive, has a Halloween pavilion in 
Palm Court featuring interactive activities including a costume contest, scary 
storytelling, face-painting, monster makeup demonstrations, costume and mask 
making, from noon to 5 p.m. today and Sunday. Admission is free. Call (818) 
622-4455. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills Youth Club sponsors its Halloween spooky house from twilight to 
11:30 p.m. at 23812 Friar St., Woodland Hills. Admission is $2 adults, $1 
children. Call (818) 888-8570. 
</P>
<P>
 Yerba Buena Elementary School, 5844 Larboard Lane, Agoura Hills, will have a 
Halloween haunted house and carnival from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. today. Activities 
include animal actors, a magic show, face painting and costume contests for 
kids from pre-kindergarten through fifth grade. Free. Call (818) 889-004. 
</P>
