<P>
VOLLEYBALL CLUB WINS 3 MATCHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Balboa Bay Volleyball Club won all three of its matches Friday to advance 
in the Sandcastle Classic International tournament in White Rock, Canada. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first match against Team Santa Cruz, Jeremy Bart had 14 kills, eight 
blocks and teammate Jody Cook-Fisher had eight kills and eight digs in the 
15-7, 15-4 victory.Matt Wright had 36 assists for Balboa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 Curtis Jackson had 10 kills and eight digs to lead Balboa in the second match, 
against a British Columbia team from Port Moody. Rob Schildts added 10 kills 
and four aces in the 15-8, 15-5 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third match, against Semiahmoo, Canada, Rawi Jackson had 15 kills and 
nine blocks and Wright had 36 assist in a 15-6, 15-10 victory. 
