<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLIPPERS; ROBERTS HAS SURGERY ON ACHILLES' TENDON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clipper center Stanley Roberts, who suffered a season-ending injury to his 
left Achilles' tendon in Wednesday night's 101-98 exhibition victory over the 
Atlanta Hawks, underwent surgery Friday at Daniel Freeman Marina Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Gene Osher, who performed the surgery, said Roberts will be sidelined six to 
nine months. 
</P>
<P>
 Roberts ballooned to more than 345 pounds after rupturing his right Achilles' 
tendon last December and was out of shape when he reported to training camp 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Coach Bill Fitch thinks Roberts won't repeat his mistake. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's learned his lesson and I think this time his rehab will be better," 
Fitch said. "I think he'll be much a better player a year from now than what we 
would have got this year." CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
