<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BEDARD'S 302 YARDS, 4 SCORES LEAD 
SERVITE BY SADDLEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Bedard gained 302 all-purpose yards and scored four touchdowns to lead 
host Servite to a 47-21 victory over Saddleback in a Golden West League 
football game Friday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The amazing thing about Bedard's evening was that it could have been a lot 
better.Two Servite penalties nullified touchdown runs of 73 and 48 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Both offenses started quickly. Bedard's 51-yard touchdown run on the game's 
third play gave the Friars (6-2, 3-0) a 6-0 lead.  
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (2-6, 0-3) wasted no time on the next drive. Quarterback Danny 
Rodriguez connected with Hector Hernandez on a 55-yard touchdown pass on the 
Roadrunners' first play. Joseph Meza's extra point give Saddleback a 7-6 lead 
with 10 minutes left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Servite's next drive ended a four-play, 55-yard drive with a three-yard 
touchdown by Bedard, giving the Friars a 12-7 lead, a lead they would not lose. 
</P>
<P>
 Servite's next score came on a 99-yard punt return by Bedard. In the first 
half, Bedard had 229 of his 302 all-purpose yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Bedard was not the only successful Friar running back. Marvin Smith rushed for 
95 yards in 14 carries and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez was 10 for 24 for 151 yards and two touchdowns and Danny Varino 
rushed for 52 yards in 14 carries to lead Saddleback. TONY ALTOBELLI 
</P>
</TEXT>
