<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALANCED TAFT BURIES CLEVELAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG ANAPOL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Jerry Brown led a balanced offense for Taft High, which 
overwhelmed Cleveland, 32-14, Friday night in a Northwest Valley Conference 
game at Taft. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, a senior, rushed 28 times for 186 yards and scored touchdowns on runs 
of 25 and 10 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft (7-1, 5-0 ) rushed for 235 yards and passed for 211. The Toreadors built 
a 25-0 lead at halftime but Cleveland (4-4, 3-2) scored two touchdowns to pull 
to within 25-14 early in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Cleveland running back Russell Burwell (19 carries, 63 yards) scored on a 
three-yard run to complete an 80-yard drive and Ramon Venegas scored on 48-yard 
swing pass from Johnny Lopez. 
</P>
<P>
 With four minutes to play, Taft embarked on a three-minute scoring drive led 
by Brown's 46 yards in nine carries. Deyon Shaw completed 11 of 18 for 188 
yards and a touchdown and tight end DaShon Polk caught four passes for 75 yards 
and a touchdown. Polk also threw a 23-yard pass for a score. GREG ANAPOL 
</P>
</TEXT>
