<HEADLINE>
<P>
HART AVOIDS FRIGHT NIGHT, 20-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It figured on the Friday night before Halloween top-ranked Hart High would get 
its biggest scare of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart's 20-7 Foothill League victory over Burbank at Burroughs High was one 
that could have turned into an upset. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart (8-0, 3-0 in league play) didn't lead by more than seven points against 
the Bulldogs (3-5, 0-2) until late in the game, when junior Ted Iacenda scored 
his third touchdown on a 12-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank, which trailed, 13-7, at halftime, had its chances. 
</P>
<P>
 Four times the Bulldogs turned the ball over inside the Hart 20-yard line. 
Quarterback Jason Jonas threw his third interception of the game on third and 
goal from the Indian six with just over six minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart depended on Iacenda's footwork because its powerful passing attack never 
got into sync. 
</P>
<P>
 Iacenda, who didn't practice all week while nursing an ankle injury, rushed 
for 141 yards and two touchdowns in 19 carries. He also caught a touchdown 
pass. BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
