<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRESPI BEATS ALEMANY, 17-7, REMAINS UNBEATEN IN LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dave Lins, the area's leading Southern Section passer, threw two touchdown 
passes and completed 18 of 24 for 174 yards to lead the Celts to a 17-7 victory 
over Alemany in a Del Rey League game Friday night at Pierce College. 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi (5-3, 3-0 in league play) leads the league and is almost assured of a 
Division I playoff berth.Alemany (1-5-2, 0-3) was held to 13 yards rushing. 
</P>
<P>
 After a 28-yard field goal by Greg Boskin opened the scoring, Lins hit Marcos 
Solorzano from six yards with 12 seconds remaining in the first quarter to give 
Crespi a 10-0 lead. The ball was tipped, first by a Celt receiver, then by an 
Alemany defensive back before falling into the arms of Solorzano in the end 
zone. On the ensuing kickoff, Crespi's Wayne Emerson recovered a fumble at the 
Alemany 24. Three plays later Lins hit Emerson from 11 yards, making the score 
17-0 early in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 After being shut out in its previous two games, Alemany finally scored on 
quarterback Rudy Pantoja's one-yard run just before halftime. The touchdown was 
set up by Ben Lovato's blocked punt. LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</TEXT>
