<HEADLINE>
<P>
HALF ENOUGH FOR HARVARD-WESTLAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Abed Abusaleh rushed for 164 yards and Hersh Davis-Nitzberg forced two key 
turnovers to lead visiting Harvard-Westlake to a 15-10 victory over St. Anthony 
Friday night in a Camino Real League game at St. Anthony. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake (6-1-1, 3-0 in league) marched 59 yards in 10 plays following 
a Davis-Nitzberg interception in the second quarter to score what held up as 
the game-winning points. The touchdown came on a 30-yard pass from Derek Lemkin 
to Kadar Lewis with 10 seconds to go before the intermission. 
</P>
<P>
 A two-point conversion pass from Lemkin to Merlin DeMartinis accounted for the 
final margin. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake ground out 277 yards while St. Anthony (6-2, 1-2) gained 137 
yards in total offense. DARIN ESPER 
</P>
</TEXT>
