<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; DIAMOND LIFTS QUARTZ HILL, 53-22 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Diamond scored five touchdowns and teammate Jeremiah Harris gained 193 
yards in 17 carries to lead Quartz Hill High to a 53-22 victory over Palmdale 
in a Golden League game Friday night at Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
 Diamond, a senior fullback, had 64 yards in 10 carries and scored on runs of 
25, two, 10, one and one yard for the Rebels (5-1-2, 2-0-1).Harris scored on a 
24-yard run in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Pereira intercepted two third-quarter passes for Quartz Hill, pitching 
to teammate Monte Reed for a 45-yard touchdown on the second one. Pereira also 
recovered two fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Johnny Gillespie of Palmdale (0-8, 0-3) rushed for two 
fourth-quarter touchdowns. He completed six of 18 passes for 94 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Olivares led the Falcons with 54 yards in 13 carries and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill quarterback Damian Kendrid attempted only four passes and did not 
complete any. But he ran for a 10-yard touchdown in the first quarter that gave 
the Rebels a 20-0 lead. STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
</TEXT>
