<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; POLY GETS OVER-PRICED, 69-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER YOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Durrell Price rushed for 238 yards and four touchdowns in only seven carries 
as Sylmar High embarrassed Poly, 69-6, in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game Friday 
night at Poly. 
</P>
<P>
 For the second consecutive week, Poly allowed its opponent to score on every 
possession. 
</P>
<P>
 On consecutive carries, Price gained 58, 65 and 75 yards -- all touchdowns. 
Sophomore Tyrone Morgan added 107 yards in five carries, including a 75-yard 
touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 The best fight Poly put up was during a brawl that delayed the game nearly 20 
minutes. Eleven players were ejected -- six from Sylmar and five from Poly. Two 
more Poly players were ejected later in the game for personal fouls. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar (8-0 overall, 6-0 in conference play) held Poly (2-6, 2-3) to minus-7 
yards rushing. Poly quarterback Ricardo Gamboa completed 15 of 29 passes for 
194 yards and a touchdown with three interceptions. PETER YOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
