SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; PACIFIC LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Muir 29, Glendale 0 -- Michael Hughes scored a pair of one-yard touchdown runs 
to spark Muir (6-2, 3-0) at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Jeremy Bonwell completed six of nine passes for 119 yards, 
including a 15-yard scoring pass to Jonothan Johnson to give Muir a 15-0 
halftime lead over winless Glendale (0-8, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Morse had 64 yards in eight carries to lead the Mustangs' ground 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale, held to 83 total yards, was led by Jason Klintworth's 42 yards in 17 
carries. Glendale quarterback Jeremy Callister was six of 12 for 52 yards and 
one interception. MIKE JOHNSON 
