</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON SANDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newbury Park 40, Camarillo 0 -- Sophomore quarterback Chris Czernek passed for 
219 yards and one touchdown to lead Newbury Park at Camarillo.Czernek completed 
nine of 15 passes. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park (5-3, 3-2) began the scoring on its opening drive, going 76 yards 
in nine plays capped by junior running back Brock Diediker's 10-yard run. The 
Panthers amassed 402 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park linebackers Chris Adams and Eric Mahanke made it a rough night 
for Camarillo sophomore quarterback Joe Borchard, sacking him eight times and 
holding the Scorpions (2-6, 0-5) to 31 total yards. JASON SANDS 
