<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FREEWAY LEAGUE; LA HABRA MAKES LATE 
STAND, HANGS ON TO EDGE FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Habra's defense was forced to stop Fullerton twice in the final 2 1/2 
minutes of the game to preserve a 27-26 victory Friday night at La Habra in 
Freeway League play. 
</P>
<P>
 After a referee's inadvertent whistle negated a Highlanders' fumble recovery, 
Fullerton running back Chris Young found Ryan Gregory with a 45-yard touchdown 
pass to pull within one point with 2 minutes 14 seconds left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians attempted a two-point conversion because Aaron Kosareff had 
already blocked two conversion attempts in the game. Gabriel Almanza was forced 
from the pocket and scrambled to the five-yard line, where he was knocked out 
of bounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton had a last chance when the Highlanders (3-5, 1-2) were forced to 
punt. With 1:19 left, Rickey Martinez intercepted a pass by Almanza and 
clinched the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra dominated the first half, jumping to a 17-0 lead after a field goal 
by Chris Diaz, a five-yard touchdown run by Johnny Yoo and a seven-yard scoring 
pass from Sonje Berg to Will McIntosh. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (4-4, 1-2) scored on a one-yard dive by John Wilkie with 29 seconds 
left in the half, but a 66-yard kickoff return by Raoul Apodaca set up a 
24-yard field goal by Diaz with one second left. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders scored again on a one-yard run by Nick Armstrong. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
