<TEXT>
<P>
 San Clemente celebrated its homecoming by defeating winless Dana Hills, 26-7, 
in front of 2,000 at San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente's defense intercepted three Scott Maynard passes, and returned 
two for touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 After a scoreless first quarter, San Clemente began to take control with Sean 
Kolmer's 20-yard interception return that gave Tritons a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
