Dolphins' punt 34 yards to put the Tritons at the Dolphins' 25-yard line. On 
that drive, Cheyenne Dixon ran in from the three-yard line to increase the 
Tritons' lead to 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 The second half began similarly for the Dolphins. Maynard was pressured by the 
Tritons' pass rush and San Clemente linebacker Robert Frith stepped in front of 
the intended Dolphin receiver and ran 41 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente (4-4, 1-2) ended the third quarter with a 20-0 lead after a 
failed conversion attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills (0-8, 0-2) tried to get its passing game working, but the Tritons' 
secondary, led by defensive backs Reagan West and Sam Kweskin kept the ball 
away from the receivers with a number of spectacular plays. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente's offense struggled to find the end zone. RICHARD MELKONIAN 
