PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SUNSET LEAGUE; COOPER'S EARLY TOUCHDOWN 
HOLDS UP FOR MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina's Steve Cooper intercepted a pass and returned it 17 yards for a 
touchdown in the first quarter to help the Vikings to a 7-6 victory over 
Huntington Beach in a Sunset League game Friday at Westminster High. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory ended a two-game losing streak for Marina (6-2, 1-2 in league).It 
was the fourth consecutive loss for Huntington Beach (1-7, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Cooper, a linebacker, rushed in on the play, grabbed Huntington Beach 
quarterback Jason Bartusick's screen pass and ran to the end zone untouched. 
The play came with 1 minute 1 second left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The 7-0 lead held up until Huntington Beach finally scored on Jason Locklin's 
three-yard sweep around the right side with 9:08 left in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Oilers lined up for an extra point try, but the play unraveled when 
Huntington Beach realized it didn't have the kicking tee. 
</P>
<P>
 First, Huntington Beach players ran to the sideline to get the tee, then 
decided to try the kick without it. But the play was rushed, the snap was 
bobbled and Marina defenders stopped the conversion attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach had another chance to win the game but Bartusick's field goal 
attempt from 42 yards was wide right with 2:49 left. He had missed from 29 
yards midway through the third quarter. KEN HILL 
</P>
