<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: RIO MESA FORFEITS ONLY VICTORY OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rio Mesa High administrators announced that the team will forfeit its Sept. 23 
game against Santa Clara for using an ineligible player. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's one of those unfortunate oversights that occur once in a great while," 
said Brian Fitzgerald, athletic director for Rio Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 "The young man in question was not an impact player. In fact he only played in 
two plays all season." 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa's only victory of the season came against Santa Clara, 36-6.  
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans drop to 0-7, 0-4 in Channel League play. Field Hockey  
</P>
<P>
 The United States Junior National Team Trials continue this weekend in the 
Field Hockey Sports Center at Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to watch the tryouts at Moorpark's artificial turf 
field, which cost $800,000 and opened last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Lenny McCauige, Olympic coach for the 1996 men's field hockey team, will be 
selecting members for the under-18 and under-21 teams. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 The Harlem Globetrotters will meet the Washington Generals in a benefit 
basketball game Sunday at 2 p.m. at Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
 The Globetrotters are training at Moorpark in preparation for a world tour. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $10 and can be purchased at the college's business center, campus 
center and basketball office. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds go to the school's athletic program. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-378-1481. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist High has an opening available in its 16-team boys' holiday 
tournament, scheduled Dec. 5-10 in the campus gym. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-884-4497. 
</P>
