<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BOLSA GRANDE MANAGES TO MAKE THE FEWEST 
MISTAKES IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AHMED V. ORTIZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Shaner scored on a pair of short runs as host Bolsa Grande defeated La 
Quinta, 14-10, Friday night in a mistake-filled Garden Grove League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Shaner, who played the second half with a broken left arm, capped a 10-play, 
66-yard march when he bulled in from one yard on fourth down for the winning 
score. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors (2-6, 1-3) were aided on the drive when the Aztec line jumped 
offside on a fourth-down punt, giving Bolsa Grande a first down. Two plays 
later on second and three, David Price found Paul Sharpe for a 36-yard 
completion. Shaner would plunge in four plays later. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta (1-7, 0-5) shot itself in the foot regularly. The game was 
epitomized near the end when the Aztecs, trying to punt the ball away, 
committed two illegal-procedure penalties. When they finally did get away a 
kick that counted, the Aztecs were flagged for unsportsmanlike conduct. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, La Quinta managed to lead at the half, thanks to Jhamal Dawkins. The 
sophomore halfback rushed for 91 yards -- or all but two of his team's total 
output -- in the first half, including a 62-yard touchdown sprint in the second 
quarter that gave the Aztecs their only lead, 10-6. AHMED V. ORTIZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
