<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; ARROWHEAD LEAGUE; SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA 
CHRISTIAN SHUT OUT AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arrowhead Christian returned two interceptions for touchdowns in the first 
half on its way to a 27-0 victory over Southern California Christian Friday 
night at Arrowhead Christian Academy. 
</P>
<P>
 SCC has now been shut out four times this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Donovan and Taylor Mast each returned passes thrown by SCC's Steve 
Schinhofen for 22-yard touchdowns, giving Arrowhead a 13-0 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Laramie Lumley led SCC (1-7, 0-3 ) with 80 yards rushing in 16 carries. The 
closest the Flames came to scoring was in the second quarter. The Flames drove 
to the Arrowhead 10-yard line, but a holding penalty and two incomplete passes 
ended the threat. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrowhead (4-4, 2-1) added two touchdowns in the second half. Matt McMurray 
caught a 40-yard touchdown pass from Clint Toth, and John Hurst scored on a 
five-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Schinhofen completed one of nine passes for 13 yards and threw two 
interceptions. He also lost two fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat Cunningham had 12 tackles and blocked extra point for SCC, his third 
blocked kick of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
