<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; FOOTHILL OVERTAKES NEWPORT HARBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman Robbie Arroyo scored three goals to help Foothill to a 7-5 victory 
over Newport Harbor in a quarterfinal game of the California State water polo 
tournament Friday at Stanford University. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Brown added two and Ryan Brown had eight saves for Foothill (18-3), the 
third-ranked team in Orange County. Newport Harbor (12-10) is ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Brown also scored four goals to lead Foothill to a 14-7 victory over San 
Jose Lynbrook in the first round earlier Friday. The Knights face Corona del 
Mar in the semifinals today. 
</P>
<P>
 In another tournament game: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 15, El Toro 8 -- Adam McFarland scored six goals and James 
Palda added five goals to lead Corona del Mar (16-4), the county's top-ranked 
team, in a quarterfinal. Neil Hueston scored six goals and McFarland and Palda 
each added two to lead the Sea Kings to an 18-6 victory over Acalanes in the 
first round. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 15, Huntington Beach 6 -- Eric Wayman scored five goals, Chad 
Bollenbach added three and Joe Huang scored two to lead host Estancia (18-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 15, Los Amigos 9 -- Bret Trezise scored eight goals to break a 
school record for single season scoring. Trezise, a senior, broke his 1993 
record of 127 by one goal. Saddleback is 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 11, Santa Ana Valley 9 -- Cesar Macedo scored five goals for Santa 
Ana (13-8). 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 15, Downey 4 -- Brian Pharris had four goals and Peter Cornue added 
three for seventh-ranked Villa Park (19-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 18, Lompoc Cabrillo 10 -- Christian Jenson scored eight goals, 
John Rootlieb and Chris Dornin each added three and Mike Marriner recorded 11 
saves to lead host Laguna Beach (18-7). 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 11, Bolsa Grande 10 -- Linh Wu's 6-0, 6-1, 6-2 sweep in No. 1 
singles was the deciding factor for La Quinta (5-4 in league). Bolsa Grande 
drops to 13-6, 4-5. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 16, Mission Viejo 2 -- The No. 1 doubles team of Lisa Panique and 
Sarah Jarrett swept its sets, 6-1, 6-0, 6-0, for Mater Dei (9-9, 5-4). 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 16, Trabuco Hills 2 -- Senior Felicity Murphy improved her league 
record to 25-2 by sweeping in singles, 6-0, 6-0, 6-0, for San Clemente (12-7, 
7-2). 
</P>
