<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST RALLY FALLS SHORT IN 13-12 LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach, the second-ranked team in the state, beat top-ranked Golden West, 
13-12, to win the South Coast League water polo championship Friday at Belmont 
Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West (23-2, 4-1) rallied for six goals in the final quarter, but it 
wasn't enough.Both of Golden West's losses this season have been against Long 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange Empire Conference: 
</P>
<P>
 Grossmont 11, Orange Coast 8 -- Jam Guiliamotti scored four goals to lead 
Grossmont (26-6, 6-0), which clinched the conference championship. Grossmont is 
the third-ranked team in the state and OCC is ranked fourth. Shad Wicker scored 
four goals and Kaj Sturdivant recorded 10 saves for Orange Coast (15-6-1, 5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 2, Orange Coast 1 -- Visiting Orange Coast became the first team to 
score against Cypress this season when Danae Fielder scored from about 20 yards 
out in the 58th minute.  
</P>
<P>
 But Cypress (12-0, 10-0) rallied to tie on a breakaway goal by Christine Tyler 
in the 77th minute. The Chargers took the lead a few minutes later when Pam 
Prine scored off a corner kick by Tracy Van Herk. It was the 15th assist for 
Van Herk this season. It was the 35th consecutive conference victory for 
Cypress, the top-ranked team in the state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
